  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Validation experiments were performed at multiple operating points; results are reported inline. Note: provenance links to generation activities are documented for the primary validation results, but one secondary result was recorded without a formal activity reference due to a data-management gap during the experimental campaign.",
